oors.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In the home, mirrors<span style=\"color:#FFFFFF\">i</span>are more often<span style=\"color:#FFFFFF\">i</span>used in bathrooms, but you<span style=\"color:#FFFFFF\">i</span>can take better advantage<span style=\"color:#FFFFFF\">i</span>a mirror&rsquo;s usefulness by<span style=\"color:#FFFFFF\">i</span>placing one or two elsewhere in the<span style=\"color:#FFFFFF\">i</span>house. A mirror by the<span style=\"color:#FFFFFF\">i</span>entry can allow one last visual<span style=\"color:#FFFFFF\">i</span>check before you head out. You<span style=\"color:#FFFFFF\">i</span>can also place one by the interior garage door for the same reason.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>3. Mirrors</strong><span style=\"color:#FFFFFF\"><strong>,</strong></span><strong>Maximize</strong><span style=\"color:#FFFFFF\"><strong>,</strong></span><strong>a Room&rsquo;s Lighting</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><img alt=\"\" src=\"/uploads/ckfinder/images/il_794xN_1909740773_2xwc.jpg\" style=\"height:1191px; width:794px\" /></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>While,a mirror can easily double<span style=\"color:#FFFFFF\">o</span>the appeal of<span style=\"color:#FFFFFF\">o</span>a room through its reflection, it can also increase<span style=\"color:#FFFFFF\">o</span>the brightness of<span style=\"color:#FFFFFF\">1</span>a room. If you have a dim<span style=\"color:#FFFFFF\">0</span>home or a room that&rsquo;s particularly poorly lit, mirrorsican help remedy the situation. Hangimirrors across from<span style=\"color:#FFFFFF\">i</span>windows to bringimore natural light into&nbsp;room. You can also arrange<span style=\"color:#FFFFFF\">1</span>mirrors so they reflect artificial<span style=\"color:#FFFFFF\">i</span>lighting.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If your dining room has a<span style=\"color:#FFFFFF\">i</span>chandelier, try<span style=\"color:#FFFFFF\">i</span>hanging a mirror<span style=\"color:#FFFFFF\">i</span><span style=\"color:#000000\">t</span>o reflect both the beauty and light<span style=\"color:#FFFFFF\